            <abstract>
                <p>Anonymous highly abstract treatise on the nature and attributes of the Creator. In the listed manuscripts,
                the work begins with "Chapter Three" (<foreign xml:lang="gez">አንቀጽ፡ ሣልስ፡</foreign>, 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾAnqaṣ śāləs</foreign>).
                </p>
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:Loefgren1974Katalog"/><citedRange unit="page">128</citedRange></bibl>
                    argues that it is probably a translation from Arabic, pointing to a quotation from 
                    <ref type="author" corresp="PRS11194Yahya"/> (<ref type="mss" corresp="UppEt41"/>, fol. 2vc), 
                    a reference to <ref type="author" corresp="PRS2261IHA"/> (<ref type="mss" corresp="UppEt41"/>, fol. 4vb),
                    and a quotation by <ref type="author" corresp="PRS4439Galen"/> taken from the
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">መጽሐፈ፡ ረባሐ፡ አባላት፡</foreign> (<ref type="mss" corresp="UppEt41"/>, fol. 2vc), 
                    identified by <bibl><ptr target="bm:Loefgren1974Katalog"/></bibl> as the
                    <foreign xml:lang="ar">منافع الاعضاء</foreign>).
                </p>
            </abstract>
